  "body": "See https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1427\r\n\r\n1. Do we separate attestation shard updates (list of intermediate state roots and block data)? Reason to do this is to avoid including unneeded data for losing attestations, increasing data efficiency.\r\n2. Block data in 128 kB chunks (for easier and more compact data availability root construction) and shard state increased from 32 bytes to 128 bytes (to allow recovery from up to 3 bad crosslinks, and to allow Merkle branch constructions to tolerate transactions created a few blocks previously)\r\n3. Slowing down shard block production if there are no crosslinks: https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/issues/1449\r\n4. Shard blocks should point directly to parents, instead of having \"empty slot filler blocks\"?\r\n5. Attestations and custody bits proposal: https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/issues/1448",
