    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "1. I'm pro separation. Plays well with #1448 \r\n2. “shard state increased from 32 bytes to 128 bytes” — not sure what you mean by the size of shard state here\r\n3. I’m in favor of the slowed down chains. at least favor this over reduction of block size/gas limit\r\n4. As discussed, having empty blocks for empty slots leads to a lot of weird scenarios and hard-to-find blocks for empty hashes. We’ve gone down this road a couple of times in the past. I don’t immediately remember all of the pitfalls but when we began to discuss in person, it seemed that we might hit them here again. I think creating a chain of just actual user-created blocks is simpler than the empty proposal, but am open to exploring it if there are any clear potential advantages\r\n5. Proposal makes sense. It does raise the max size of some objects other than just the attestations — AttesterSlashing of note. puts it in the ~300kb range instead of ~50kb. Seems fine but need to keep it in mind",
